<p>This endpoint join user to multiple groups. It can also be used for community admins to add a user to multiple groups.</p>
<h3 id='http-request-8'>HTTP Request</h3>
<p><code class="request">POST /api/v1/users/:id/groups</code></p>
<h3 id='url-parameters-2'>URL Parameters</h3>
<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Parameter</th>
<th>Default</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>id</td>
<td></td>
<td>The ID of user to join (add)</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h3 id='request-parameters'>Request Parameters</h3>
<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Parameter</th>
<th>Default</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>groupIds</td>
<td></td>
<td>List of the groups&#39; IDs to join</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2 id='join-multiple-groups'>Join Multiple Groups</h2><pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code>curl <span class="s2">"https://community.tribe.so/api/v1/user/groups"</span>
  -H <span class="s2">"Authorization: Bearer {access_token}"</span>
  -X POST
  --DATA <span class="s2">"{...}"</span>
</code></pre><pre class="highlight javascript tab-javascript"><code><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">require</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'tribe'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="kd">let</span> <span class="nx">api</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">tribe</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">authorize</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'{access_token}'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nx">api</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">group</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">join</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">'groupId'</span><span class="p">]);</span>
</code></pre>
